// Phase 2.7 fixture #1 — thesis §Primitive 4 example 1, verbatim.
//
// THE LOAD-BEARING DEMO FIXTURE. The canonical mizan block: a
// detector calibrating against false-positive rate (la_tatghaw —
// the do-not-transgress upper bound), detection rate (la_tukhsiru
// — the do-not-make-deficient lower bound), and a calibration
// function reference (bil_qist — establish in justice).
//
// The shape is exactly what Bayyinah's detector calibration pattern
// produces in production: every detector ships with three values
// calibrated jointly because tightening the upper bound typically
// loosens the lower bound (FRaZ non-monotonicity, Underwood et al.
// 2020). The mizan block is the language-level transposition.
//
// Expected: parses cleanly, well-formedness checker returns zero
// marads. Both thesis examples (this one and compression_ratio)
// pin the canonical shape.

bismillah CalibrationDemo {
    authority: NAMING_MD
    serves: purpose_hierarchy.balance_for_living_systems
    scope: calibrate
    not_scope: nothing_excluded
}

mizan detection_threshold {
    la_tatghaw:  false_positive_rate < 0.05
    la_tukhsiru: detection_rate > 0.90
    bil_qist:    calibrate(corpus, paired_fixtures)
}
